election_record.label: Vermont 1822 Council

overview.note: "It is a novel circumstance, in our Councillor election to have two chosen from one town. Messrs. Hatch and Proctor both live in Cavendish in this county. Rutland County has no Councillor this year - the division of the vote between their three candidates, Messrs. Mason, Warner and Williams, prevented the election of either - 65 votes more for Mr. Mason would have given him the election over Mr. Proctor." Woodstock Observer (Woodstock, VT). October 15, 1822.

sub_unit.name: Addison
sub_unit.note: The original election returns report 751 votes for Truman Chittenden, 654 for Timothy Stanley, and 566 for Jabez Proctor. The town votes in these original returns, however, add up to the totals listed here.

sub_unit.name: Limington
sub_unit.note: In Limington, 2 votes for Charles Williams have here been credited to Charles K. Williams.
